      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CALATHINITE (1) showed early speed from an outside draw last time then tired over the final stages to finish seventh, beaten 5 lengths, over 1200m at this track. Expected to measure up here. Worth another try. GINGERIFFIC (10) has not appeared since she finished fourth over 1200m at this track on May 9. Sure to make her presence felt. WORKING CLASS GIRL (9) showed good early dash before weakening to finish sixth over 1103m at Roebourne last time out. Bold showing expected this time around. CHANTILLY GIRL (5) recorded her maiden win four back and is ready to score again after a couple of recent minor placings, the latest when second at this track. Has a high cruising speed. Should give backers a sight. RAY'S SAUCE (3) was too good at Marble Bar last time out and can go on with the job.",
